ood of Unreal Engine</title>\n		<link>https://visible.si/hood-unreal-engine/</link>\n		<comments>https://visible.si/hood-unreal-engine/#respond</comments>\n		<pubDate>Tue, 19 Sep 2017 11:11:00 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mitja Prelovsek]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Sandbox]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Games]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[interactive]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[ue4]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Visible media]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://visible.si/?p=21863</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://visible.si/hood-unreal-engine/">Under the Hood of Unreal Engine</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://visible.si">VISIBLE</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div   class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid js-master-row  mk-fullwidth-false attched-false ">\n	<div style="" class="vc_col-sm-12 wpb_column column_container ">\n			<div class="mk-text-block responsive-align-center  "><p>Unreal Engine is our favourite game engine. And every now and then a project comes along which gives us an opportunity to look under its hood and use features that are not often used. In our latest project (soon coming to the work page) we had to find a way to render scene depth and object segmentation. Have a look!</p>\n<div class="clearboth"></div></div> \n	</div></div>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://visible.si/hood-unreal-engine/">Under the Hood of Unreal Engine</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://visible.si">VISIBLE</a>.</p>\n]]></content:encoded>\n			<wfw:commentRss>https://visible.si/hood-unreal-engine/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>L+D Magazine, July 2017</title>\n		<link>https://visible.si/ld-magazine-july-2017-2/</link>\n		<comments>https://visible.si/ld-magazine-july-2017-2/#respond</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 09 Aug 2017 11:59:51 +0000</pubD